### Phase 0 — manual checks (REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP)
# Environment: select `dev` in http-client.env.json; start server with Postgres or `--spring.profiles.active=dev`.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@phone = +233241234567

### Health (no auth)
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

### Send OTP — happy path
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{phone}}"
}

### Send OTP — invalid number (expects 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "07911123456"
}

### Send OTP — rate limit smoke (run 4× same number, 4th expects 429)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{phone}}"
}

### Verify OTP — happy path (use OTP from dev console log)
# Replace 123456 with the OTP printed by [DEV] log when dev-log-otp=true
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{phone}}",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### Verify OTP — wrong code (expects 400 INVALID_OTP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{phone}}",
  "otp": "000000"
}

### Verify OTP — invalid format (expects 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "{{phone}}",
  "otp": "abc"
}

### GET /me — authenticated profile + entitlements
# Replace <token> with the accessToken from verify-otp response
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me
Authorization: Bearer <token>

### GET /me — no token (expects 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me
